 <td valign="top" class="vt-content">
 

	
  <div class="vt-datebar">
  <a href="./viewtopic.php?p=7609#p7609"><img src="./styles/absolution/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>Posted: Thu Oct 20, 2011 8:51 am 
  </div><!-- /vt-datebar --> 
            
       <div class="vt-postcontent">
       As a follow up my stora is online with a 3TB partition RAID1.<br /><br />Since I created the array incorrectly the first time I had to manually remove the old array and re-create it.  then i realized that using ext3 with the default block size still only allows 2TB  <img src="./images/smilies/embarrassed.gif" alt=":-[" title="Embarrassed" /> .  so after tons of re-sysncing and re-formatting i had to format like this (i'll edit above)<br /><br />./mkfs.ext3 -b 4096 /dev/md0<br /><br />There was also no /etc/mdadm.conf file (maybe because i screwed around so much) so I had to create one manually to allow the array to persist reboots. I did this in this way:<br />mdadm -Q --detail --brief /dev/md0 &gt; /etc/mdadm.conf<br /><br />you can create the file manualy, but it sucks to try and type in the UUID
       </div> 
       
       

    
    
 </td><!-- /content -->
